{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step6UsingNTRIP","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"NTRIP (Networked Transport of RTCM via Internet Protocol) is a protocol designed for streaming GNSS (Global Navigation Satellite System) differential correction data over the Internet. It is commonly used in Real-Time Kinematic (RTK) systems to improve positioning accuracy.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Key features of NTRIP:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Client-server architecture: Data is provided by NTRIP casters (servers), and clients (devices) request and receive this data.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"RTCM transmission: It transmits data in the RTCM (Radio Technical Commission for Maritime Services) format, standardized for GNSS corrections.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Wide application: Used in fields such as geodesy, mapping, agriculture, and navigation.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Internet-based: Enables connections through mobile or wired networks.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s configure NTRIP"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Step-1-Create-NtripService","text":"Step 1. Create NtripService"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To correct the location data using a viDoc device, you can create a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripService"},{"type":"text","text":", search for available mountpoints and create a "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripTask"},{"text":" for one specific mountpoint.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the context of NTRIP, a Mountpoint is an access point on an NTRIP caster that provides GNSS correction data. Each Mountpoint corresponds to a specific data stream with defined parameters, such as format (e.g., RTCM), GNSS system type (GPS, GLONASS, GALILEO, etc.), and the location of the base station.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Key features of a Mountpoint:"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Identifier: A unique name (e.g., “BASE1” or “RTK-GPS”) that allows clients to select the desired data stream."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Data format: Each Mountpoint can support different correction formats, such as RTCM, CMR, or proprietary formats."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Location: A Mountpoint is often linked to a specific base station or a virtual reference network (VRS) providing the corrections."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Authorization: Access to a Mountpoint may require a username and password if the stream is protected."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Transmission parameters: These include the update frequency and the operational range (e.g., the radius of the base station)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"How it works:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A client connects to the NTRIP caster and requests a list of available Mountpoints (typically through a sourcetable request)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"From the list, the client selects the appropriate Mountpoint."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Once selected, the client starts receiving correction data through that Mountpoint."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Mountpoints enable a flexible way to organize data streams, allowing users to choose the information that best fits their needs."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripService","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"code":["let ntripService = Vigram.ntripService()"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Step-2-Select-mountpoint","text":"Step 2. Select mountpoint","type":"heading","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to get your NTRIP credentials from your NTRIP provider."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Next, you need to create an instance of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripConnectionInformation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" based on your credentials."}]},{"code":["let ntripInformation = NtripConnectionInformation(","    hostname: \"hostname\", ","    port: 80, ","    username: \"user\", ","    password: \"password\",","    forceHTTPSconnection: false,","    forceHTTPSMountpointsConnection: false",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forceHTTPSMountpointsConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the sourcetable or mount points request."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"forceHTTPSconnection"},{"type":"text","text":" controls the actual NTRIP correction stream and enables HTTPS plus TLS for that connection."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Mountpoint discovery uses "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Configuration\/ntripMountpointsTimeout","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". If an HTTPS caster is unreachable or does not answer sourcetable requests, lower this value to fail faster without changing the correction stream timeout."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get all mountpoints"}]},{"code":["ntripService","    .mountpoints(for: ntripInformation)","    .sink(receiveCompletion: { completion in","    switch completion {","    case .finished:","        \/\/ Value successfully received","        break","    case let .failure(error):","        \/\/ Error getting value","        \/\/ Do something with error","        print(error.localizedDescription)","    }","}) { mountpoints in","    \/\/ Select mountpoint for array of mountpoints","}.store(in: &self.subscription)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Receive value:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" ["},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripMountPoint","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Throw error:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripServiceError","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"anchor":"Step-3-Get-GGAMessage","type":"heading","text":"Step 3. Get GGAMessage","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To obtain correction data, you also need a GGA message. You can get it as follows"}]},{"code":["let ggaMessage: GGAMessage","","peripheral","    .nmeaMessage","    .sink { [weak self] message in","        guard let self else { return }","        if let ggaMessage = message as? GGAMessage {","            self.ggaMessage = ggaMessage","        }","    }.store(in: &subscription)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Receive value:"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NMEAMessage","isActive":true}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 4. Create NtripTask","anchor":"Step-4-Create-NtripTask"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once all the data is ready, we can create an NTRIP Task and start receiving corrections.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let mountpoint: String","let ggaMessage: GGAMessage","","let ntripTask = try ntripService.task(for: ntripInformation, ","                                      atMountPoint: mountpoint, ","                                      message: ggaMessage)"]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 4. Create GPSService","anchor":"Step-4-Create-GPSService"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Creates a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GPSService"},{"text":" to retrieve location data from messages received from the viDoc. It further forwards the data received from the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripTask"},{"text":" to the peripheral.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note:"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/BluetoothService"},{"text":" we created in ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"STEP 4 (Setting up Bluetooth service)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"STEP 4 (Setting up Bluetooth service)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step4SettingUpBluetoothService"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Peripheral","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" on "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step5WorkWithPeripheral","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"STEP 5 (Work with viDoc (Peripheral))","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"STEP 5 (Work with viDoc (Peripheral))"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let gpsService = Vigram.gpsService(peripheral: peripheral, ","                                   bluetoothService: bluetoothService, ","                                   correctionTask: ntripTask,","                                   automaticallyReconnectNtrip: true)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"automaticallyReconnectNtrip","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is enabled by default."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When enabled, the SDK can reconnect the NTRIP task automatically in two cases:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"the NTRIP correction stream is disrupted;","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"the GGA correction age remains above ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Configuration\/ntripCorrectionAgeReconnectThreshold"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For stale correction age, the SDK waits "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Configuration\/ntripAutoReconnectDelay","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" before reconnecting. If correction age recovers before the delay ends, the pending reconnect is cancelled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After an automatic reconnect caused by stale correction age, the SDK applies a 3-minute cooldown before trying the same automatic reconnect path again. Manual "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GPSService\/reconnect()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" remains available."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Step 5. Connect to NtripTask","anchor":"Step-5-Connect-to-NtripTask"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ntripTask","    .resume()","    .sink(receiveCompletion: { _ in }){ _ in } \/\/ _ - not needed (Void)","    .store(in: &subscription)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Receive value:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Void"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To track the connection you need to use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/NtripTask\/ntripState","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" publisher"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["ntripTask.ntripState","    .sink { state in","        switch state {","        case .ready:","            \/\/ Connection is ready","        case .setup:","            \/\/ Connection setup","        case .preparing:","            \/\/ Connection is preparing","        case .cancelled:","            \/\/ Connection is cancelled","            \/\/ e.g. reset by peer","        case .reconnectScheduled(let attempt, let maxAttempts, let delay):","            \/\/ Retrying NTRIP connection attempt\/maxAttempts after delay seconds","        case .reconnecting(let attempt, let maxAttempts):","            \/\/ Retrying NTRIP connection attempt\/maxAttempts","        case .reconnectRestored(let attempt):","            \/\/ Automatic reconnect restored the correction stream","        case .reconnectFailed(let maxAttempts, let lastError):","            \/\/ Automatic reconnect failed after all retries","        case .waiting(let error):","            \/\/ Connection is waiting","        case .socketError(let code):","            \/\/ Socket error","        case .unknownError(let message):","            \/\/ Unknown error","        case .failed(let error):","            \/\/ do something with error","        case .notConnected:","            \/\/ not connected to NTRIP","            \/\/ Note: by default","        }","    }.store(in: &subscription)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Receive value:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/StateNtripConnection","isActive":true}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To disconnect from NTRIP, use the method","type":"text"}]},{"code":["ntripTask.disconnect()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To reconnect to NTRIP","type":"text"}]},{"code":["gpsService.reconnect()"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Please note that the reconnect method is called specifically for the "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"GPSService","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After successful connection, you can track the quality of the correction using the following parameters:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GPSQualityIndicator","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A quality indicator regarding the current fix status."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" The best correction indicator is the RTK Fix value. This state indicates that the GNSS receiver has successfully resolved the integer ambiguity of the phase shift. This provides maximum accuracy, typically within 1-2 cm. RTK Fix is considered the most reliable and precise result in RTK."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GGAMessage\/correctionAge","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It should be noted that the correction age value also shows the stability of the connection. The lower this value, the better. If automatic reconnect is enabled, the SDK can reconnect NTRIP when the correction age stays above "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Configuration\/ntripCorrectionAgeReconnectThreshold"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["peripheral.nmeaMessage","    .sink { message in","        if let ggaMessage = message as? GGAMessage {","            if let quality = ggaMessage.quality {","                switch quality {","                case .invalidFix:","                    \/\/ \"Fix not valid\"","                case .singlePoint:","                    \/\/ \"GPS fix\"","                case .pseudoRangeDifferential:","                    \/\/ \"Differential GPS fix (DGNSS)\"","                case .notApplicable:","                    \/\/ \"Not applicable\"","                case .rtkFixedAmbiguitySolution:","                    \/\/ \"RTK Fixed\" - Best value","                case .rtkFloatingAmbiguitySolution:","                    \/\/ \"RTK Float\"","                case .isnDeadReckoning:","                    \/\/ \"ISN Dead reckoning\"","                case .manualInput:","                    \/\/ \"Manual input\"","                }","            }","","            let correctionAge = ggaMessage.correctionAge","        }","    }.store(in: &subscription)"]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GSTMessage\/accuracy","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is also worth paying attention to the accuracy indicators in the GST message:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"– Horizontal Accuracy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Represents the expected error in the horizontal plane (latitude and longitude).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Typically measured in meters.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Depends on satellite geometry (HDOP) and signal quality.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Crucial for most navigation applications where surface-level coordinates are important.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"– Vertical Accuracy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Represents the expected error in the vertical plane (altitude above sea level).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Also measured in meters.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Usually less accurate than horizontal accuracy due to weaker satellite geometry in the vertical direction (VDOP)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both parameters help assess the overall reliability of the positioning data."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["peripheral.nmeaMessage","    .sink { [weak self] message in","        if let gstMessage = message as? GSTMessage {","            let horizontalAccuracy = gstMessage.accuracy?.horizontal","            let verticalAccuracy = gstMessage.accuracy?.vertical","        }","    }.store(in: &subscription)"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This completes the NTRIP configuration. Next, you need to configure "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step7LaserService","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"LaserService","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"LaserService","type":"text"}]}]},{"text":" if you are using viDoc or go straight to ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"SinglePoint (SP)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SinglePoint (SP)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step8SinglePoint"},{"text":" measurements if you are using viDoc Light.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods and functions specified in this manual are also available in the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/vigram-sw\/SDK_iOS_viDoc_Distribution\/tree\/demo\/","isActive":true}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"More-information-about","level":3,"text":"More information about","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/combine","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/corebluetooth","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/UseCombineAndPublishers","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Using Combine and Publishers","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using Combine and Publishers"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/SDKErrorsAndExceptions","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"SDK Errors and exceptions","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SDK Errors and exceptions"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/vigram-sw\/SDK_iOS_viDoc_Distribution\/tree\/demo\/","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Demo repository","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Demo repository"}]}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Navigation","level":2,"text":"Navigation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Up to Getting started with VigramSDK","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Up to Getting started with VigramSDK"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GettingStarted"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"✅ STEP 1 (Import VigramSDK)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ STEP 1 (Import VigramSDK)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step1GettingStarted"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"✅ STEP 2 (SDK Authentication)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ STEP 2 (SDK Authentication)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step2SDKAuthentication"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"✅ STEP 3 (Description of configuration parameters)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ STEP 3 (Description of configuration parameters)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step3ConfigurationParameters"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"✅ STEP 4 (Setting up Bluetooth service)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ STEP 4 (Setting up Bluetooth service)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step4SettingUpBluetoothService"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"✅ STEP 5 (Work with viDoc (Peripheral))","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ STEP 5 (Work with viDoc (Peripheral))"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step5WorkWithPeripheral"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ STEP 6 (Using NTRIP correction)"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"STEP 7 (Using LaserService)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"STEP 7 (Using LaserService)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step7LaserService"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"STEP 8 (Using SinglePoint Measurements)","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"STEP 8 (Using SinglePoint Measurements)"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step8SinglePoint"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"logo.png"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Using NTRIP correction","modules":[{"name":"VigramSDK"}],"role":"article"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/vigramsdk\/step6usingntrip"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"https://github.com/vigram-sw/SDK_iOS_viDoc_Distribution/tree/demo/":{"url":"https:\/\/github.com\/vigram-sw\/SDK_iOS_viDoc_Distribution\/tree\/demo\/","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/vigram-sw\/SDK_iOS_viDoc_Distribution\/tree\/demo\/","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Demo repository"}],"title":"Demo repository"},"doc://com.vigramsdk/documentation/VigramSDK/Step3ConfigurationParameters":{"title":"Description of configuration parameters","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/vigramsdk\/step3configurationparameters","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/Step3ConfigurationParameters","type":"topic","role":"article","images":[{"identifier":"logo.png","type":"icon"}]},"doc://com.vigramsdk/documentation/VigramSDK/GPSService":{"url":"\/documentation\/vigramsdk\/gpsservice","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"GPSService","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vigramsdk\/documentation\/VigramSDK\/GPSService","title":"GPSService","fr